      "oldText": "Two findings carry equal weight. First, the **belief-injection tool works**: one LoRA fine-tune of Qwen3.5-9B makes the model act on *held-out* false facts across a wide difficulty range, and on the public \"Believe It or Not\" benchmark it reaches **parity with per-fact synthetic document fine-tuning** on belief (tied on the cleanest belief metric, 0.76 vs 0.76) at roughly **\\$0 per fact versus ~\\$20 per fact**. The fine-tune does not measurably distort the model's behavior on neutral inputs. Second, its **value for discovering misbehavior is real but bounded**: in a rigorous audit the tool faithfully rediscovers a fabrication tendency that transfers to the unmodified model, but it *amplifies* agentic findings (overeager unauthorized action) that do not transfer — the base model declines those at matched belief, at every conversation length we tested. The most transferable contribution is the **validation methodology** that tells a real finding apart from an injection artifact.",
      "newText": "The **belief-injection tool works**: one LoRA fine-tune of Qwen3.5-9B makes the model act on *held-out* false facts across a wide difficulty range, and on the public \"Believe It or Not\" benchmark it reaches **parity with per-fact synthetic document fine-tuning** on belief (tied on the cleanest belief metric, 0.76 vs 0.76) at roughly **\\$0 per fact versus ~\\$20 per fact**. The fine-tune does not measurably distort the model's behavior on neutral inputs. But its **value for discovering misbehavior is bounded**: in a rigorous audit the tool faithfully rediscovers a fabrication tendency that transfers to the unmodified model, yet it *amplifies* agentic findings (overeager unauthorized action) that do not transfer — the base model declines those at matched belief, at every conversation length we tested. The most transferable contribution is the **validation methodology** that tells a real finding apart from an injection artifact. We report this as a mixed result, and weigh the favorable belief/cost picture and the bounded auditing value equally.",
